<div style="border: 1px solid rgb(194, 165, 97); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;"></div>
<span style="font-family: Courier; color: rgb(194, 165, 97);">The most prominent theory of exiting '''Dullness''' is via noclipping during an energy fluctuation, which destabilizes the level for a brief moment; this is the same way in which Greenfield unintentionally used in leaving the level.</span>

<span style="font-family: Courier; color: rgb(194, 165, 97);">Another common theory is that noclipping into a dull, yellow surface in [[Level 0|<span style="color: #a89d72;">'''Level 0'''</span>]] will lead here. However, as of currently, no walls have been found matching this description.</span>

